        verification storyIndicatorTypeDoD : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-b092-51627384bd02"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Add the general Indicator model (D0089; ISO-15939/PSM/SMM), generalizing my git-only first cut per the human's correction. SCHEMA (frozen unfreeze, human sign-off; SCHEMA_ORDER + _ID_TYPES updated): schema/core/indicator.sysml = part def Indicator (measures/goal/unit/method/collectionRef) + part def Measurement (value/measuredAt/source) + enums IndicatorGoal{minimize,maximize,observe} + MeasurementMethod{computed,pulled,manual}. An Indicator informs by DIRECTION (D0088), excluded from assurance/orphan required-edge sets (no verify/satisfy). TOOLING: view.rs indicators(root,trend) + indicator_status + measurement_series (source-agnostic: computed series via headline_at/trend_series; pulled/manual from #Measures-linked Measurements); main.rs cmd_indicators; write.rs append_measurement + main.rs cmd_record_measurement (#Measures edge). PROCESS/SKILL/VIEWPOINT: .engine/processes/indicator.sysml + indicator skill + skills-registry + indicators viewpoint. INSTANCES: 3 computed (coverage/velocity/volatility -> report headlines) + 1 pulled (avRegulationCount + 2 seed Measurements) + 1 manual (authoringFriction + 2 seed Measurements — the friction case, now first-class showing 'improving'). d0089 #ProspectiveChange keystone + Core-3 critiqued; doc-sync CLAUDE.md/usage.md. VERIFY: validate_schema 15/15; validate_instances 104/104; rust validate 105 (the .tracking authority, D0048 — Indicator/Measurement types resolve, only the pre-existing marker-edge kernel limit remains); `sysmlv2 indicators` shows all 3 methods (authoringFriction 4->2 improving, avRegulationCount 42->47 observed, computed current values); record-measurement appends + validates; clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings + cargo test (43 lib, +indicator_status_is_direction_aware) + guard all (12) green."; }
