    verification indicatorTypeImplementGate : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-b092-51627384bd08"; :>> title = "Sprint 92 implement gate"; :>> createdAt = "2026-06-22"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::test; :>> procedureText = "Implemented schema + tooling + process/skill/viewpoint + instances + D0089 + critiques + doc-sync. VERIFY (live): validate_schema 15/15 (incl indicator.sysml); validate_instances 104/104 (incl d0089 + indicator process); rust validate 105 clean; `sysmlv2 indicators` = authoringFriction 4->2 [manual/improving], avRegulationCount 42->47 [pulled/observed], coverage 100% / velocity 281 / volatility 0 [computed]; record-measurement appended a datapoint the view picked up; clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings green; cargo test 43 lib pass; guard all (12) PASS (after adding 'indicators' to VIEW_SUBCOMMANDS — caught by viewpoint-renderer->assured cascade). The Indicator/Measurement types resolve in the kernel; only the pre-existing marker-edge limit (Verify/Resolves/Measures/Informs) remains in validate_tracking, which is non-authoritative (D0048)."; }
